<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Tossed and turned. Always happens whenever we're exploring someplace new.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  I understand. Well, if there's nothing more, Captain, I'm eager to get back to work. We have another twenty million cubic kilometres to chart.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Sorry to keep you. I'm afraid you'll be working alone today.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  Oh?</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Sub-Commander T'Pol's in Sickbay. From what the doctor tells me, she's in pretty bad shape.</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  That's unfortunate. What happened?</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You know damn well what happened. She told me about your, what did she call it, mind-meld? She said when she asked you to stop, you got angry. She said she had to force you away.</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  What happened between us is personal. It's not your concern.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You assaulted a member of my crew.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  I did no such thing. Mind-melds can be emotionally turbulent. She simply panicked.</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Panic doesn't land you in Sickbay. Our doctor said she could have suffered neurological damage, thanks to you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  No one forced her to try the meld. She did it willingly.</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>ARCHER:  You've been manipulating her ever since you came aboard.</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  I am helping her shed a lifetime of repression, and you of all people should understand what I'm trying to do. You're human. I need to go see her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>ARCHER:  T'Pol's had enough of your help. Stay away from her.</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  She is in a crucial stage of her awakening. She needs guidance.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>ARCHER:  I told you, it's over.</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  I think that's for her to decide.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>ARCHER:  Maybe I'm not making myself clear. Sickbay's off-limits.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  You're in my way, Captain. You'd be wise to let me leave.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>ARCHER:  What's wrong, Tolaris? Getting angry? I thought you had that under control.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>TOLARIS:  (grabbing Archer) Move aside.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>ARCHER:  T'Pol's right. You've got a temper.</td></tr>

